<HEADLINE>
FT  25 JUN 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In general the pepper markets were rather slow this week in the absence of
fresh buying of forward positions. The price of white pepper declined
marginally to about USDollars 2,775-2,800 a tonne, cif, for August/December
shipment from origin. Spot white pepper commanded apremium of some USDollars
150 a tonne, which was regularly paid for smaller lots. Black pepper prices
were under little pressure from rpoducer offerings and remained fully
steady. Here too smaller lots were traded on the spot market at about
USDollars 1,700 a tonne, mainly for the fair average quality grades.
