FT  25 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Bullers anticipates return to the black
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Bullers, the giftware and decorative products group which earlier this year
expanded into media services, yesterday reported pre-tax losses of Pounds
1.23m for the six months to December 31.
The deficit, which included losses of Pounds 284,000 from discontinued
operations, compared with losses of Pounds 1.42m for the year ended June 30
1993 and was struck on turnover of Pounds 1.6m (Pounds 2.43m).
Mr David Cunningham, chairman, stressed that the 'poor' outcome preceded the
acquisition of Clashfleet for a maximum Pounds 2.8m, funded by a placing and
open offer, and a substantial capital reorganisation and debt conversion.
