FT  25 JUN 94 / Venezuelans warned of economic controls
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOSEPH MANN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CARACAS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Venezuelan government is close to adopting 'harsher measures' to deal
with critical economic, financial and monetary problems, Mr Julio Sosa,
minister of finance, told congressmen, writes Mr Sosa, the leading economic
policymaker in the administration of President Rafael Caldera, did not
specify what these measures would be but he indicated the administration
could declare a 'state of economic emergency'. This would give the executive
branch the power to dictate extraordinary economic and financial measures to
confront an economic crisis.
Many Venezuelans, alarmed by a deteriorating economy, expect the government
to take steps soon to impose price controls on basic consumer goods.
